body: The package directory doesn't exist because the build failed earlier. Is there an error message saying why building activations_impl.cu failed?

> /home/yian/ONNX1.12.0/onnxruntime/cmake/external/onnx-tensorrt/onnx2trt_utils.hpp: In function ‘nvinfer1::IConstantLayer* onnx2trt::addConstant(onnx2trt::IImporterContext*, const std::vector&, onnx2trt::ShapedWeights::DataType, nvinfer1::Dims)’:
/home/yian/ONNX1.12.0/onnxruntime/cmake/external/onnx-tensorrt/onnx2trt_utils.hpp:119:21: error: ‘class nvinfer1::INetworkDefinition’ has no member named ‘setWeightsName’; did you mean ‘setName’?
ctx->network()->setWeightsName(weights, weights.getName());

I would suspect there's a version mismatch between TensorRT and something. See https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/execution-providers/TensorRT-ExecutionProvider.html for combinations that work.

This is probably also relevant for the `constexpr` errors: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/12683#issuecomment-1224504597

@skottmckay  I was going crazy. I followed the tutorial steps. Jetpack 4.6.1,  g++ version 7.5,  cmake version 3.23.0
